            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <p><!--external apparatus criticus (if applicable)--></p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>The flame-fleeing brothers, the greatest gifts of pietas, whom conflict carried off – these Merulus has returned, vir clarissimus et spectabilis (most noble and respectable), consular governor of the province of Sicily.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="it" resp="#SA">
                <p></p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>The text records a base for the Fratres Pii / Fratres ambusti, famous rescuers of their parents from eruption of Etna and heroes of Catania. They appear on coinage from the hellenistic period onwards. The original statue may have dated back to hellenistic times, with the fragmentary inscription on the reverse of the earlier imperial period perhaps belonging to an earlier instance of the base, which may have stood in the forum, rather than the theatre.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" xml:lang="it">
                <p></p>
            </div>
